headline: GM Leans on Nvidia for Self-Driving Tech
summary: General Motors is deepening ties with the world’s leading computer-chip firm, Nvidia, in hopes of improving its autonomous-driving technology and manufacturing operations. GM will use Nvidia’s in-vehicle computer for future advanced driver-assistance systems.

headline: Nvidia, GM partner on next-gen AI for self-driving cars and factory robotics
summary: At Nvidia's GTC event, the chipmaker added another big automaker to its list of auto partners. "I'm super-excited to announce that GM has selected Nvidia to partner with them to build their future self-driving fleet," CEO Jensen Huang said. "The time for autonomous vehicles has arrived, and we’re looking forward to building with GM AI for three areas — AI for manufacturing, AI for enterprise for how they work, and AI for in the car."
